function minTotalCost(startPos, homePos, rowCosts, colCosts) {
    const rowDifference = Math.abs(startPos[0] - homePos[0]);
    const colDifference = Math.abs(startPos[1] - homePos[1]);

    let rowCost = 0, colCost = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < rowDifference; i++)
        rowCost += rowCosts[i + Math.min(startPos[0], homePos[0])];
    for (let i = 0; i < colDifference; i++)
        colCost += colCosts[i + Math.min(startPos[1], homePos[1])];

    return rowCost + colCost;
}
```

    The algorithm tries to solve the problem by first calculating the absolute differences in rows and columns of the `startPos` and `homePos` arrays. Then, it calculates the respective costs for rows and columns by summing up the values in the `rowCosts` and `colCosts` arrays starting from the minimum row and column position of `startPos` and `homePos` up to the row and column difference. Finally, the algorithm returns the sum of the row and column costs.

